  <mads:note type="source">Brill's New Pauly: "Pausanias, Greek lexicographer, contemporary of Aelius Dionysius [21] of Halicarnassus, 
    from the time of Hadrian (beginning of the 2nd cent. AD). Like Dionysius, P. is known as the author of an alphabetically ordered,
    fragmentarily handed-down Atticistic dictionary with the title Ἀττικῶν ὀνομάτων συναγωγή ...."</mads:note>
